snippet: The 2016 race creates a challenge, brought home on a busy weekend of campaigning: Is there such a thing as too many presidential candidates?
abstract: New Hampshire Republicans feel overwhelmed by number of presidential candidates visiting their state hoping to win votes in Republican primary; many are dismayed that there is no obvious front-runner among 16 contenders.

byline.original: By PATRICK HEALY and MAGGIE HABERMAN
byline.contributor: Patrick Healy reported from Amherst, and Maggie Haberman from Wolfeboro, N.H.

lead_paragraph: The 2016 race creates a challenge, brought home on a busy weekend of campaigning: Is there such a thing as too many presidential candidates?

headline.main: New Hampshire Voters Bemoan Size of G.O.P. Field
headline.print_headline: Size of G.O.P. Field Hinders New Hampshire in Role as National Screener
